          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-400">Dialect</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Origin</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why UG Is SOWPODS-Only</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ SOWPODS Includes</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Dialectal English verbs, archaic terms, regional British/Scottish words that have fallen out of common use but remain in historical dictionaries.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ TWL Excludes</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Words without widespread modern North American usage. UG hasn't entered mainstream American English, so NASPA keeps it out of the Tournament Word List.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy: Playing UG in SOWPODS Games</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">U-tile relief:</span> U is often a burden tile — it pairs poorly and you can get stuck with multiple U's. UG lets you dump a U productively in SOWPODS games, scoring 3 while clearing rack space.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Front hooks:</span> BUG (6pts), DUG (5pts), HUG (7pts), JUG (11pts), MUG (6pts), PUG (6pts), RUG (4pts), TUG (4pts). JUG at 11 points is a standout hook — leave UG accessible if you have a J.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">UGH extension:</span> UG extends to UGH (7pts) — a valid word in both dictionaries. If you play UG first, extending to UGH next turn adds the H(4) value.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">⚠️ Important Rule</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Always confirm your dictionary <span class="text-white font-medium">before the game starts</span>. Online platforms usually state which dictionary is in use. In tournaments, it's announced at the start. Playing a SOWPODS-only word in a TWL game loses your turn.</p>
      </div>

